The defendant Janelle M Autry was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Child Abuse-Intentionally Cause Harm, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.03(2)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Janelle M Autry in court with attorney Leah R. Thomas.  Benjamin Calvin Verhulst appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Probation Agent is in court.  Probation Status Review report filed and reviewed.  Defendant is compliant with probation.  The remaining condition time is stayed.  Court found that further review is not needed.

Defendant Janelle M Autry in court with attorney Leah R. Thomas.  Matthew James Torbenson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Statements made as to sentencing.
The Court sentenced defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT OF 4 YEARS, with credit for 1 day time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS.  
.
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program; is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
.
Court IMPOSED BUT STAYED the Sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 3 years with the following conditions:
-Defendant to serve 60 days  in the House of Correction, STAYED, until next court date.
-Complete an anger management course.
-Complete a parenting class.
-Complete a program for victims of trauma.
-No violent contact with any child; no corporal punishment or the use of implements.
-Comply with all orders of children's court and MBCW.
-No controlled substances without a valid prescription.
-Random urine screens.
-Cooperate fully with probation agent.
-Pay all court costs, assessments and fees in this action during period of Probation, or to be docketed as a civil judgment.
.
